FTSE 100 Stocks Slide as Irish Regulators Set Banks’ Capital Requirements

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-03-31T15:40:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/ftse-100-stocks-slide-as-irish-regulators-set-banks-capital-requirements.html
U.K. stocks fell in the final
minutes of trading as Irish regulators said four banks need to
raise 24 billion euros ($34 billion) in additional capital
following stress tests on the nation’s lenders.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index dropped 0.7 percent to
5,908.76 at the 4:30 p.m. close in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  